  "body": "## Motivation\r\nI have come across a few scenarios where I can't get the raw revert data I need to test my contracts.\r\n\r\nRevert, in accordance with EVM standard, has no formal return specification, i.e. it's not always strings from Solidity.\r\n\r\nIt would be nice if Buidler handled non-standard reverts.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nWhen testing add the ability for it to throw with a rich error, including revert codes, transaction hashes etc.\r\n\r\nCurrently the Error is weak, with a simple message and no further data about the revert. The console only shows some data but it is unreachable in code terms.\r\n\r\nHere we add `revert` and `transactionHash` properties. As well this allows me to wrap these calls with different `expect` handlers and deal with my non-standard reverts easily.\r\n\r\n```js\r\ntry {\r\n   await erc20.transfer(ethers.constants.emptyAddress, 500);\r\n} catch (error) {\r\n   console.log(error.revert.code);\r\n   console.log(error.transactionHash);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
